<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17470429-35">
               <interp inst="t17470429-35" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17470429-35" type="year" value="1747"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17470429-35" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17470429"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17470429-35" type="date" value="17470429"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17470429-35-off152-c283" targOrder="Y" targets="t17470429-35-defend352 t17470429-35-off152 "></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17470429-35-off152-c284" targOrder="Y" targets="t17470429-35-defend354 t17470429-35-off152 t17470429-35-verdict155"></join>
         
               <p>221, 222. + 
               
                  <persName id="t17470429-35-defend352" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Exelby 
                  <interp inst="t17470429-35-defend352" type="surname" value="Exelby"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-defend352" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-defend352" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
                
             and 
               
                  <persName id="t17470429-35-defend354" type="defendantName">
                     William 
                     Smith 
                  <interp inst="t17470429-35-defend354" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-defend354" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-defend354" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
                
             (and 
               <persName id="t17470429-35-person355">
                  Thomas 
                  Waterman 
               <interp inst="t17470429-35-person355" type="surname" value="Waterman"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person355" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person355" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             not taken) were indicted for <rs id="t17470429-35-off152" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-off152" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-off152" type="offenceSubcategory" value="theftFromPlace"></interp>
               stealing two Pieces of striped Silk Cotton, value 28 s. fifteen Yards of Seusee, value 33 s. thirteen Yards of checked Linen, value 7 s. the Goods of 
                     
                        <persName id="t17470429-35-victim357" type="victimName">
                           Elizabeth 
                           Morgan 
                        <interp inst="t17470429-35-victim357" type="surname" value="Morgan"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17470429-35-victim357" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17470429-35-victim357" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17470429-35-off152 t17470429-35-victim357"></join>
                     </persName>
                      
                  , out of her Dwelling-House
            </rs>, <rs id="t17470429-35-cd153" type="crimeDate">November 29</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17470429-35-off152 t17470429-35-cd153"></join>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17470429-35-person358">
                  Elizabeth 
                  Morgan 
               <interp inst="t17470429-35-person358" type="surname" value="Morgan"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person358" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person358" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in <placeName id="t17470429-35-crimeloc154">Brook's-Market, in St Andrews Holbourn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17470429-35-crimeloc154" type="placeName" value="Brook's-Market, in St Andrews Holbourn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17470429-35-crimeloc154" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17470429-35-off152 t17470429-35-crimeloc154"></join>; on the 29th of November I missed these Goods mentioned in the Indictment, about Eight o'Clock in the Morning.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="174704290034"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t17470429-35-person359">
                  John 
                  Harford 
               <interp inst="t17470429-35-person359" type="surname" value="Harford"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person359" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person359" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . About a Month before Christmas, I went with the two Prisoners to this Woman's House, and they bored a Hole in the Wall big enough to pull out the Goods that have been mentioned.</p>
               <p>Harford, the Witness, produced some Scraps of checked Linen, and as Exelby told him were the Pieces of Linen they then stole.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17470429-35-person360">
                  Elizabeth 
                  Morgan 
               <interp inst="t17470429-35-person360" type="surname" value="Morgan"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person360" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person360" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             swore that they were like her Linen, but one may be like another.</p>
               <p>Harford likewise acknowledged they took out some Pieces of Worsted, about a Pound Weight of each.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17470429-35-person361">
                  Elizabeth 
                  Ruff 
               <interp inst="t17470429-35-person361" type="surname" value="Ruff"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person361" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person361" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Mr. Harford came to my House lost Shrove-Tuesday Night; when he came in, he bid me put the Child out of Doors, and he cried prodigiously, and said, I am ruined for ever, for Exelby will hang me and my Wife too; he says, do you know any thing of my Wife? I said, if I did, I would not let him know, for Fear he would murder her; he said if Smith did not let him have his Wife, he would have his Life, if he sent his Soul to Hell.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17470429-35-person362">
                  Elizabeth 
                  Crooks 
               <interp inst="t17470429-35-person362" type="surname" value="Crooks"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person362" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person362" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have known Smith ten or a dozen Years, and I never heard a dishonest Character of him in my Life.</p>
               <p>Q. What is Smith?</p>
               <p>Crooks. He is a licensed Hawker.</p>
               <p>Tucker. Smith has the general Character of an honest Man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17470429-35-person363">
                  Mary 
                  Tosman 
               <interp inst="t17470429-35-person363" type="surname" value="Tosman"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person363" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person363" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have known 
               <persName id="t17470429-35-person364">
                  William 
                  Smith 
               <interp inst="t17470429-35-person364" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person364" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person364" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             these six Years, he has a very honest Character as far as ever I knew.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17470429-35-person365">
                  Jeremiah 
                  Anderson 
               <interp inst="t17470429-35-person365" type="surname" value="Anderson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person365" type="given" value="Jeremiah"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person365" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have known him seven Years, and he has borne a good Character.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17470429-35-person366">
                  William 
                  Smith 
               <interp inst="t17470429-35-person366" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person366" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-person366" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             
                  <rs id="t17470429-35-verdict155" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17470429-35-verdict155" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               acquitted
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>[As Exelby was capitally convicted before, the Merits of the Cause, with Respect to him was very little examined, any more than to give Light to the other.]</p>
            </div1>
